/*
    Process tables for the "happy" test adventure.

    These files are a worked example of the condacto language defined in
    docs/specs.md. All processes use the universal two-token header
    `<slot1> <slot2>:`. The meaning of each slot per table:

        init       _ _                                   (all "_ _")
        location   <loc|*>   _
        response   <verb|*|_> <noun|*|_>
        cron       <HOURS|MINUTES|SECONDS|TURNS> <n>
        npc        <noun|*>  <adj|*|_>

    They reference labels that exist in the rest of the happy/ source:

      Locations: celda, celda3, vestíbulo, cuartelillo, gradas, exterior,
                 muerte, tumba, …
      Items:     ant-on, ant-off, talismán, denario, bolsa, cofre,
                 llave1, llave2, petaca, ropa, cinturón
      Characters: player (human), enano, elfo
      Words:     coger, dejar, abrir, cerrar, examinar, decir, ir, fin, …
                 norte, talismán, bolsa, cofre, antorcha, denario, llave, …
      Vars:      turns, score, hunger (global)
                 celda.visited, exterior.visited (per-location)
                 ant-on.on, player.health,
                 enano.patience, enano.death, elfo.hidden
      Messages:  intro, low-health, dead, hungry, starving, dwarf-grunt,
                 dwarf-rage, elf-cry, elf-hidden, torch-on, torch-off,
                 no-here, score-msg, end-game, storm, chest-shut,
                 chest-opened, empty-bag, new-location, get-ok, get-nook,
                 drop-ok, wear-ok, wear-nook, unwear-ok, unwear-nook,
                 have, have-nothing, havent, worn, ok, bye, sure, cant,
                 cant-do, loc-objects

    All of the above already exist in the other happy/*.inc.adv files,
    EXCEPT a handful of blob labels (`ambient`, `prison-pic`, `city-pic`)
    that appear in PLAY/PICTURE calls. Those would live in a SECTION
    PICTURES that does not yet exist in happy.

    The compiler does not yet parse SECTION TABLES, so this folder is
    intentionally NOT included from test.adv. When the parser lands, add
    to test.adv:

        INCLUDE "proc/tables.inc.adv"

    Author: queru (github.com/queru) 2026
*/

SECTION TABLES

INCLUDE "init.inc.adv"
INCLUDE "location.inc.adv"
INCLUDE "response.inc.adv"
INCLUDE "cron.inc.adv"
INCLUDE "npc.inc.adv"
